A woman has been arrested with 500 grammes of cocaine valued at Sh2.5 million at her house in Komarocks. The woman in her 40s was found with 46 pellets of the narcotic that she had packaged and planned to send to Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. She was presented before JKIA court where police were allowed to hold her until today when she will take plea. In the past one month, narcotics valued at Sh40 million have been recovered. &nbsp;